<DOC><DOCNO> AP890502-0192 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-02-89 2007EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Peru     05-02 0123</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Peru,0127</SECOND><HEAD>Soldiers Kill 15 Leftist Guerrillas</HEAD><DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Soldiers on patrol in the Andes encountered aband of leftist guerrillas and killed 15 in a firefight, thegovernment said Tuesday.   A government statement said the battle took place Monday nearVischongos, 215 miles southeast of Lima in Ayacucho state, and onesoldier also was killed.   Security forces have reported killing more than 100 guerrillasin the past month.   The statement said the soldiers encountered an undeterminednumber of guerrillas from the Shining Path, a Maoist group whoseinsurgency began in Ayacucho nine years ago, but gave no details.   Officials say more than 14,000 civilians, rebels, policemen andsoldiers have been killed since the Shining Path began fighting in1980.</TEXT></DOC>